# ERD ↔ Codebase Alignment Audit

> **ERD Source:** `ERD.md` (19 domain tables + 2 security tables)
> **Files checked:** `models.py`, `web_controller.py`, `auth_controller.py`, `rpi_controller.py`, `otp_service.py`, `middleware.py`, `seeder/seed.py`, `seed.py`, `__init__.py`

---

## Models vs ERD — Field-by-Field

### ✅ Fully Aligned (15/21 entities)

| ERD Entity | Model | Verdict |
|---|---|---|
| `ORG_TYPES` | `OrgType` | ✅ Exact match |
| `ORGANIZATIONS` | `Organization` | ✅ Exact match |
| `ORG_ADDRESS` | `OrgAddress` | ✅ Exact match |
| `ORG_CONTACT` | `OrgContact` | ✅ Exact match |
| `COMMUNITY_GROUPS` | `CommunityGroup` | ✅ Exact match |
| `USERS` | `User` | ✅ Exact match |
| `WALLET` | `Wallet` | ✅ Exact match |
| `OTP_CODES` | `OtpCode` | ✅ Exact match |
| `RVMS` | `RVM` | ✅ Exact match |
| `RECYCLING_SESSIONS` | `RecyclingSession` | ✅ Exact match |
| `RECYCLING_ITEMS` | `RecyclingItem` | ✅ Exact match |
| `TRANSACTIONS` | `Transaction` | ✅ Exact match |
| `REWARDS` | `Reward` | ✅ Exact match |
| `REWARD_REDEMPTIONS` | `RewardRedemption` | ✅ Exact match |
| `MAINTENANCE_LOGS` | `MaintenanceLog` | ✅ Exact match |
| `ADMIN_LOGS` | `AdminLog` | ✅ Exact match |
| `BULK_DEPOSITS` | `BulkDeposit` | ✅ Exact match |
| `NOTIFICATION_SETTINGS` | `NotificationSetting` | ✅ Exact match |
| `NOTIFICATION_LOGS` | `NotificationLog` | ✅ Exact match |
| `TOKEN_BLACKLIST` | `TokenBlacklist` | ✅ Exact match |
| `LOGIN_ATTEMPTS` | `LoginAttempt` | ✅ Exact match |

### ⚠️ Mismatched (1 entity)

| ERD Entity | ERD Field | Model Field | Issue |
|---|---|---|---|
| `USER_SECURITY` | `two_factor_enabled` | `two_factor_enabled` | ✅ Model correct |

> The ERD and model agree. But `seed.py` uses `two_fa_enabled=False` (lines 417, 486) — a field that doesn't exist. This will silently be ignored by SQLAlchemy (keyword arg not matching column name), meaning **2FA is never properly set during seeding**.

### ⚠️ `REWARD_VARIANTS` — 2 Field Mismatches in Seeder

| ERD Field | Model Field | Seeder Field | Issue |
|---|---|---|---|
| `variety_name` | `variety_name` ✅ | `label` ❌ (line 527) | Seeder uses wrong field name. Will crash or silently ignore. |
| *(not in ERD)* | *(not in model)* | `is_default=True` (lines 528, 667) | Field does not exist on `RewardVariant` model. Will crash on query (line 667). |

---

## 🔴 Runtime Bugs (will crash or produce wrong results)

### Bug 1 — `web_controller.py:1934` — `RecyclingItem.condition` doesn't exist

```python
RecyclingItem.condition    # ← Column removed in new ERD
```
ERD says `status` (Accepted/Rejected). No `condition` field.

> [!CAUTION]
> Analytics endpoint `GET /api/web/analytics` will crash with `AttributeError`.

**Fix:** Replace `.condition` with `.status` on lines 1934, 1935, 1940, and in the response serializer at lines 2052-2055.

---

### Bug 2 — `web_controller.py:1949` — `Account` model referenced

```python
total_users_base = db.session.query(func.count(User.id)).join(Account).join(CommunityGroup)
```

> [!CAUTION]
> `Account` is not imported and doesn't exist. `NameError` crash on analytics endpoint.

**Fix:** `db.session.query(func.count(User.id)).join(CommunityGroup)`

---

### Bug 3 — `web_controller.py:2735-2751` — `get_login_history()` uses removed `Account` model + old field names

```python
.join(Account, User.account_id == Account.id)                    # ← Account removed
.join(CommunityGroup, Account.community_group_id == CommunityGroup.id)  # ← Account removed
.order_by(AdminLog.timestamp.desc())                              # ← field is created_at
...
'timestamp': _dt(l.timestamp),                                    # ← field is created_at
```

> [!CAUTION]
> `NameError: Account` + `AttributeError: timestamp`. Login history endpoint completely broken.

**Fix:** Replace with `User.community_group_id → CommunityGroup` join, use `AdminLog.created_at`.

---

### Bug 4 — `web_controller.py:457` — `filter_by(org_type_id=ot_id)` wrong column name

```python
ref_count = Organization.query.filter_by(org_type_id=ot_id).count()
```

Model uses `type_id`, not `org_type_id`. SQLAlchemy `filter_by` with wrong field name will raise `InvalidRequestError`.

> [!CAUTION]
> Delete org-type endpoint crashes.

**Fix:** `filter_by(type_id=ot_id)`

---

### Bug 5 — `web_controller.py:774,780,781` — Undefined `name` variable

```python
_log_action(current_user, 'User Created', name, 'Users', f'Role: {role}')   # name undefined
trigger_alert(location_id, 'new_user_registered',
              f'New user registered: {name}',                                  # name undefined
              f'A new {role} "{name}" was created by {current_user.name}.')   # name undefined
```

> [!WARNING]
> `NameError` when creating user via `POST /api/web/users`.

**Fix:** Replace `name` with `user.name`

---

### Bug 6 — `seeder/seed.py:527-528` — Wrong `RewardVariant` field names

```python
variant = RewardVariant(
    reward_id=reward.id, label='Default',         # ← model field is variety_name
    stock_quantity=r['stock'], is_default=True,    # ← is_default doesn't exist
)
```

> [!CAUTION]
> Seeder will crash when creating reward variants.

**Fix:** `label='Default'` → `variety_name='Default'`, remove `is_default=True`

---

### Bug 7 — `seeder/seed.py:667` — Queries non-existent `is_default` field

```python
variant = RewardVariant.query.filter_by(reward_id=reward.id, is_default=True).first()
```

> [!CAUTION]
> Seeder crash during redemption seeding.

**Fix:** `filter_by(reward_id=reward.id, variety_name='Default')`

---

### Bug 8 — `seeder/seed.py:417,486` — Wrong `UserSecurity` field name

```python
sec = UserSecurity(user_id=user.id, two_fa_enabled=False)
```

Model field: `two_factor_enabled`. `two_fa_enabled` silently ignored → no error, but 2FA state never explicitly set.

> [!WARNING]
> Not a crash (SQLAlchemy ignores unknown kwargs), but semantically wrong.

**Fix:** `two_fa_enabled=False` → `two_factor_enabled=False`

---

