## ERD / Model Design Justification

### ✅ What the New ERD Does Well

| Design Decision | Justification |
|---|---|
| **`Wallet` separated from `User`** | Single-responsibility. Point mutations don't lock the User row. `lifetime_points` enables O(1) leaderboard reads without aggregating transactions. `streak` lives where points live — coherent domain boundary. |
| **`UserSecurity` separated from `User`** | 2FA settings change independently from profile. Avoids bloating the most-queried table with rarely-read columns. Clean extension point for future MFA methods. |
| **`OtpCode` as persistent table** | Survives server restarts. Works across multiple Gunicorn workers. Auditable — you can answer "how many OTPs did user X burn through?" |
| **`OrgAddress` + `OrgContact` (1:1 + 1:N)** | Replaces old `City` lookup table. Flat address strings avoid join overhead. 1:N contacts supports orgs with multiple PICs — realistic for universities. |
| **`RecyclingItem` ML-native fields** | `detected_class` + `confidence_score` directly maps YOLOv8 output. No more legacy `brand`/`volume_ml`/`condition` fields that don't exist in an ML pipeline. `status` (Accepted/Rejected) is the only decision the system makes. |
| **`RewardVariant` per-SKU stock** | Stock tracked at variant level (Red-Medium, Blue-Large) instead of a single number per reward. Matches real inventory management. `variety_name` is descriptive. |
| **`BulkDeposit` dedicated table** | Admin manual deposits have their own audit trail separate from RVM sessions. `admin_user_id` tracks who approved it. |
| **`Transaction` with structured references** | `reference_type` + `reference_id` (integer) replaces old string-based `description`/`reference_id`. Enables programmatic joins back to source records. `balance_before`/`balance_after` gives full audit trail. |
| **`RecyclingSession.wallet_id`** | Direct FK to Wallet. Old schema went `Session → Account → User → points`. New schema: `Session → Wallet`. One less join, cleaner. |
| **`MaintenanceLog.status` enum** | `Resolved/Pending/Cancelled` replaces boolean `resolved`. Can now express "we gave up on this repair" without deleting the record. |
| **`AdminLog.created_at`** | Standardized timestamp naming across all tables. No more `timestamp` vs `created_at` inconsistency. |
| **`RVM.is_capacity_full` boolean** | Maps directly to IR sensor output (HIGH/LOW). Old `current_capacity` integer was meaningless — the sensor doesn't report percentages. |
| **`User.community_group_id` direct FK** | Removes the `Account` indirection layer. Old: `User → Account → CommunityGroup`. New: `User → CommunityGroup`. Every scoped query is 1 join cheaper. |
| **`LoginAttempt` table** | Security monitoring with `ip_address`, `failure_reason`, `attempted_at`. Supports configurable lockout policies per org. |
| **`TokenBlacklist`** | JWT revocation on logout. `expires_at` enables cleanup cron jobs. |

### ✅ Improvements Implemented

| Gap | Change | Status |
|---|---|---|
| **No `deactivated_at` on `User`/`Reward`** | Added `deactivated_at DateTime` to both `User` and `Reward` models + ERD | ✅ Done |
| **No `avatar_url` on `User`** | Added `avatar_url String(500)` to `User` model + ERD | ✅ Done |
| **No `image_url` on `RewardVariant`** | Added `image_url String(500)` to `RewardVariant` model + ERD | ✅ Done |
| **No OTP attempt counter** | Added `attempts Integer default 0` to `OtpCode` model + ERD | ✅ Done |
| **`OrgContact` global phone/email uniqueness** | Changed from global `UNIQUE` to org-scoped `UniqueConstraint('organization_id', 'email')` and `UniqueConstraint('organization_id', 'phone_number')` | ✅ Done |
| **`NotificationSetting` dual-purposed** | Kept as-is — acceptable trade-off to avoid schema bloat. No code change needed. | ⏭️ Deferred |

### ⏭️ Skipped (By Design)

| Gap | Reason |
|---|---|
| **No session duration analytics** | Not needed — `end_time - start_time` can be computed at query time. Keep schema lean. |
